.TH "i40iw_find_sd_index_limit" 9 "i40iw_find_sd_index_limit" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
i40iw_find_sd_index_limit \- finds segment descriptor index limit
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "void" i40iw_find_sd_index_limit
.BI "(struct i40iw_hmc_info *hmc_info "  ","
.BI "u32 type "  ","
.BI "u32 idx "  ","
.BI "u32 cnt "  ","
.BI "u32 *sd_idx "  ","
.BI "u32 *sd_limit "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "hmc_info" 12
pointer to the HMC configuration information structure
.IP "type" 12
type of HMC resources we're searching
.IP "idx" 12
starting index for the object
.IP "cnt" 12
number of objects we're trying to create
.IP "sd_idx" 12
pointer to return index of the segment descriptor in question
.IP "sd_limit" 12
pointer to return the maximum number of segment descriptors
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
This function calculates the segment descriptor index and index limit
for the resource defined by i40iw_hmc_rsrc_type.
